                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.48/915: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-02T18:00:00+04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 3, 3:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1358. Department’s telegram number 717, July 22 [<hi rend="italic">23</hi>], 4
                    p.m. For reasons given in my 1357, August 2, 5 p.m.<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d720fn46">Transmitted in telegram from the Ambassador in Great
                        Britain, no. 2687, Aug. 3, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> steamer <hi rend="italic">Redondo</hi> should not proceed to Archangel.
                    The British have sent flour which is now here and are sending more which will
                    suffice until evacuation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
